FBIS4-5656 "dreas071_a_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-071 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Bank Plans To Extend Untied Loans to Peru Bank Plans To Extend Untied Loans to Peru OW1304084694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0803 GMT 13 Apr 94 OW1304084694 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 13 KYODO -- The Export-Import Bank of Japan will extend two untied loans worth 22.5 billion yen to Peru, bank officials said Wednesday [13 April]. A signing ceremony for the loans took place Tuesday at the annual meeting of the Inter-American Development Bank in Guadalajara, Mexico. The loans will go toward improving the country's infrastructure. It is the first time for the bank to extend an untied loan to the country.
